    expect(classifyContent('{"a":{"b":{"c":1}}}')).toBe('json');
  });
});
```

**Acceptance criteria:**
- `classifyContent('{"key":"value"}')` returns `'json'`
- `classifyContent('[1, 2, 3]')` returns `'json'`
- `classifyContent('\x1b[32mSuccess\x1b[0m')` returns `'ansi'`
- `classifyContent('Hello world')` returns `'plain'`
- `classifyContent('{"command":"ls')` returns `'plain'` (partial JSON)
- ANSI detection takes priority over JSON when both are present
- Empty string returns `'plain'`
